o do it (or u eBayed!), here's some Q &amp; A for running or participating in a AE group. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Why would a level 60 need to still do AE groups?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Few reasons would be obviously for Luclin, XPing again will gain the ability to put points in skill tress to further accentuate your wizard. Then there is also loot, dot funding, powerleveling friends and guildies. But the best factor of all, nothing beats the looks on a meatshields face when he sees 2 wizards kill 20 mobs in under 1 minute. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Who should I invite to make my AE group?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Group dynamics are very important for an AE group. You have to have at least 2 nukers and 1 enchanter. Having a healer for the puller is also highly regarded as required.<br>
<br>
For the nukers, wizards are the main players. However, mages can be substituted as well if high enough level to cast Point Blanks. Necros and Clerics can also do damage if the mobs being pulled are undead. <br>
<br>
For the Stunners, it's generally known only Enchanters will do. Their PBAE stun is the glue that holds together the group. This uses low mana and they can chain cast it. Without this, the wizards would be dead in seconds. This is also why level of mobs being pulled is key to the enchanter as resists will have them killed quite quickly. As well, having 2 enchanters is usually the safest bet for an AE group with a large appetite as spacing will have the enchanter running around to stun and will create chaos, which in a PBAE group will get everyone killed. <br>
<br>
For the healers, go with a cleric. They can AE heal during fights and will need quick small heals for the puller while he stacks. Shamans and druids can also be substituted. <br>
<br>
For the puller, the main thing you need is someone with a few things. Knowledge of the zone, testicular fortitude and be able to die and not be too concerned. Pulling quality trains is a skill not all that many meatshields have. I've used paladins the most and they seem to get the job done quite well with their skills. Rangers and SKs work well but really any melee can do it if they have the guts (and the HP/buffs). The main thing you need for the puller is for him/her to understand their role. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Uhh..well, what is the pullers role?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Grab as many as you can, bring them back to the group and stand STILL. Let them stack as neat as possible so that the enchanters can begin the stun chain. Once the stuns land and you get your baby heal, GO GET MORE. Ensure that all mobs brought to camp stay stacked neatly and you've done a perfect pull. With 2 enchanters, they can cast their PBAE stuns for roughly a minute while a second train is pulled, just another reason Enchanters are an integral part of the PBAE groups. The Puller should then sit back and engage/finish off any stragglers or out of range mobs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The healer just sits there like an xp sponge? WTF!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Don't they wish. A healer must always be ready when healing a PBAE group. First the puller, when the incoming is about to come, a small heal should be used (Celestial Healing I believe?) so that aggro isn't gained and the puller stays alive, once the stuns begin aggro will be lost by the puller and they can go grab part 2 of the pull. The enchanters will then most likely need some small heals as well for any mobs that resist the stuns. If the enchanter is of lower level than the mob, resists will play a large part in the healers mana consumption. The wizards shouldn't be much to worry about, while aggro will be then taken during the nuke phase, absorption skins should keep them unharmed for the chain casting of the nukes. This is dependant on the mobs engaged. Of course, clerics are needed to rez the puller who will know doubt, die a few times with too large of trains.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> What do the wizards do to kill all those mobs so fast?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Around the wizard circle, it's pretty well known Al'Kabor is NOT a wizard of great merit. Namely because he is a pompous Erudite who has the crappiest line of AE spells ever created in Norrath. However, another Wizard named Jyll created a line of high level wizard spells that create a Point Blank Area Effect when cast. Now this is a wizard! This line of spells has unlimited targets available as long as their in immediate reach. General rule of thumb when casting these is, STAND IN THE MIDDLE OF ALL THE MOBS. They will all be chain stunned, they won't hit you..much. <br>
<br>
I keep all these up when AEing; Jyll's Wave of Heat, Jyll's Zephyr of Ice and Jyll's Static Pulse. Because of short recast times, these can easily be chain cast just using 2. After a few casts, you will not be able to lose aggro so ensure you stay situated between all mobs so that they can stay stacked. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I got my group together, where do we go to AE?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
There are some very quality locations to PBAE in, but some places have little differences that can cause delays and problems for your group. I'm sure other people can give creative feedback on other hunting grounds for this so I'll list a few of my favorites. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Sebillis</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Alot of people who have tried to PBAE here will have horror stories I'm sure, it's a little bit more difficult as the mix between casters/knights and the movement of the frogloks is a pain to get them to stack properly. Ensure your group knows what they're doing before attempting frogs. Loot and XP is quite good when emploring PBAE here however.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Karnors Castle</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Great place to train PBAE enthusiasts. Mobs are a bit lower level so resists usually aren't an issue. With new teal con's, XP will still flow even for 60's. Recommended to either pull to VS stage room or Basement. If KC crowded, the basement is usually empty and has a ton of undead mobs. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Velketor's Labyrinth</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Only camp I have AE'ed is the Pit and the entrance. The Pit is all dogs. Really easy to pull trains down there but is a chance resists could happen. Loot isn't great but the plat payout is. Spiders are really easy if enough can be found, however remind the puller to not turn his back on 10 backstabbers. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Howling Stones</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A favorite of PBAE groups for a number of reasons. The place is usually empty, groups can clean all 4 wings in a night and get great loot and even better XP. Few problems that can hamper you though. Alot of the mobs Harm Touch which will kill your puller numerous times when attempting trains. As well as traps can hamper movement. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Chardok</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Very fun place to AE. You will never run out of mobs to pull, can use other AE tricks (like Fearing one so it brings back 30 others) and the loot/plat/xp is also excellent. Can AE right down to royals as well if your group can handle it. Fast repops, some HT's and alot of named piled in the trains can cause messy CR's. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The Hole</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Wouldn't recommend it. Golems can't be stunned and your chanters will be dead quite quickly attempting it. You'll always get a few golems in a train. Mages I hear, are great down here. They can make their own godamn PBAE groups then <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Plane of Fear</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
This of course, would be a raid event however AE is a very easy way to clear this plane so that setup for golems or CT is nice and fast. Key to  success, stacking and informing melees not to block out the PB classes. 60 chanters and wizards are also recommended. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> City of Mist</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Never tried it myself but I'm sure it'd be possible, just don't get Reavers in your pulls!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Droga</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
With the new Chardok Ring being introduced alot of level 60s now frequent this mid level dungeon and not just for the Idol of the Thorned. Getting Chardok faction is a high priority now and this is the only way to get it. Since alot of lvl 60s will have maxed -Sarnak, they will need to kill 3000+ goblins in Droga and what better way than AE! large dungeon and some Gob's HT but since a bit lower level (30s?) any puller worth their weight shouldn't have a problem with this. Give him rune and lev and should be able to pull 30 at a time with relative ease. Of course, no Xp down here if you are 60. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LGuk/SolB</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
This was a good place to learn how to train AE in Dungeons and I am sure they're still quite viable alternatives but I haven't returned to them to PBAE in ages so will let someone else give hints for these zones. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> What do you mean by &quot;stacking&quot; ?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The key to a successful PBAE group hinges on this. If the mobs are spread out, they won't die and when you're OOM at the end of a fight and there is still 5 mobs left, and you remember you only have one melee in your group well...<br>
<br>
When you have undead in the trains, ENSURE that the puller stands in front of the group to stack as undead will attack whatever is closest.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> What about downtime?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Occasionally you'll expend your entire mana bar but since you'll have at least one enchanter there, that shouldn't be a problem should it. If it is, bring a bard to pull, thhey can do it with aggro songs and mana song you during downtime. Either way, nuke until they're all dead or you will be.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> We keep dying. It's all your fault, how you gonna make it up to us!?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
PBAE groups are risky, no matter where you do it. When you have 20 mobs in camp, anything can happen. Once you learn how to execute flawlessly, you'll see downtime isn't even an issue. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> How many mobs can be pulled per train?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
It matters on the puller, levels of the participants and the zone you're in. For the puller, if they can DA or have a buttload of hit points, maybe they can get enough in the first run but if not, then the strategy of enchanters stunnin for the 2nd train should be used. Remember, the more in the train the more productive your group is. But use common sense. Just because your PBAE group can kill 15 skellies in the KC basement doesn't mean you'll have the same luck with Amy Knights in Fear. So for some trains, stick to the general rule: 8 Is Enough. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.packetlost.com/ho/eq/AEFear.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Can wizards pull for PBAE groups?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Yup, and cutting out the melee puller actually adds more firepower to the group. I'd recommend it be an epic'ed wizard as the skin is what will keep him/her alive. As well, pull small trains and let the chanters hold it, reskinning between each pull. Don't bother with HT mobs unless you have a deathwish. Flux staff will be tough to pull so many so fast, use aggro via distance instead to cut down on the number of hits you'll absorb. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Any tricks you know of for PBAE groups?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I'm sure others have found some stuff to help out with different aspects of PBAE groups. Hrmm, can't really think of many offhand. You can use your Eye of Zomm to pull random trains in dungeons by casting it through the wall, but you never know what you'll get this way and will sometimes aggro an entire dungeon and/or multiple bosses and get many people outside of your group killed. You can also use Fear spells and aggro radius spells to pull, but due to cast times, sometimes these aren't useful. <br>
<br>
There is some tricks you can use with mob paths and aggro to make them bring the entire zone to you. Who would of known how simple it was to make a train like this as a newbie<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.packetlost.com/ho/eq/frogtrain.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
And of course, don't try PBAE groups in places it won't work *cough* <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.packetlost.com/ho/eq/wipeout.wmv">www.packetlost.com/ho/eq/wipeout.wmv</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Anyways, hope it helps if you haven't done AE groups before and feel free to post your own hints and tricks and/or questions and remember STAND STILL! Only 3 mobs can ever hit you at a time, don't be afraid to AE!<br>
