<br>
A mage will not do as the 2nd caster, their spell does not recycle as fast as a wizards for AE.  They will make an excellent 3rd caster and have a score of other functions to really help out like CoH, mod rods for epic wizards, damage shields and pets.<br>
<br>
Cleric/Paladin pull.  DA/DB rule for pulling and highly recommended way of getting the mobs to camp.  Once in camp it will be hard to lose agro.<br>
<br>
Epic Wizards or Runed wizards are VITAL.  If you dont have an epic, bring lots of dots.  While the rune is up, it is considerably easier to channel through.  I have tested this extensively and unless the mob has a nasty bash you will most likely channel through.  Think of it as you are the main tank, call out AE time, control the party.<br>
<br>
If the enchanter dies you die.  Runed and fully buffed.  Aego if possible.  Do not damage shield the enchanter!!<br>
<br>
Discuss the route the puller will take.  Best way is to run to a pre determined pull spot.  Only AE on 10 or more or it is just not efficient for mana reasons.  Mez, get more and remez until you get the tight group.<br>
<br>
SOW/Jboot the puller.  Another good reason to have a mage, he can CoH the puller in after he zones and jboots/SOWs up.<br>
<br>
Advanced Techniques:<br>
<br>
Everyone in the party turn off all graphics, /showspelleffects off.  One nice Winds of Geild and you can lag yourself to death.<br>
<br>
CE the puller prior to grabbing mobs.  When the mobs come to the group, CE/Torpor/Heal over time the enchanter.<br>
<br>
If you are real confident of the pathing, send in a pet or fear a mob into a crowd.  Tricky as the worst possible thing you can do is have a staggered train.<br>
<br>
For a single mob, paladin stun &gt; enchanter stun due to the damage.  If you accidently pull a boss mob, have the paladin go to town on the boss and solo tank/ chain stun until the fray is done.  Paladins also have wave of healing as an added bonus.<br>
<br>
Decession is wonderful with a CoH mage.  Allows the puller to be anyone.  You send the puller to zone, get Sowed (spend the money on the potion) and CoH the puller back.  You dont have to depend on a druid.<br>
<br>
60 wizards and a semi staggered pull, start off with winds of geild.  The reason is HUGE damage as a taunt.  Takes a little practice in timing but 1200hps of damage single shot will keep the mobs off the enchanter everytime and the range is huge for this spell.  It is a mana hog and has no use after the inital pull due to cast time.  If you mez park all mobs open up with this spell.  It will bring the mobs closer to you and away from the enchanter.<br>
<br>
